definitions.definition: Tending to create things, or having the ability to create; often, excellently , in a novel fashion , or any or all of these.
examples: a creative dramatist who avoids cliche
a creative new solution to an old problem

definitions.definition: A type of set of natural numbers , related to mathematical logic .
Designed or executed to deceive or mislead.

main_definition: Tending to create things, or having the ability to create; often, excellently , in a novel fashion , or any or all of these.
secondary_definitions: ( of a created thing ) Original , expressive and imaginative .
